Leaves it, he blows. Stays, he drowns.
Let's get out of here.

764
01:16:31,424 --> 01:16:33,813
- Tarconi.
- They have the girl.

765
01:16:34,560 --> 01:16:38,047
Frank, we are trying to track him
through the phone signal.

766
01:16:38,048 --> 01:16:40,666
- Where are you?
- In a lake.

767
01:16:41,376 --> 01:16:43,416
A lake?

768
01:16:43,424 --> 01:16:45,407
Can you be more specific?

769
01:16:45,408 --> 01:16:47,098
There's a dam.

770
01:16:48,224 --> 01:16:50,271
- A dam?
- I know the place, sir.

771
01:16:50,272 --> 01:16:52,224
- How far?
- Ten minutes at least.

772
01:16:52,225 --> 01:16:54,176
Frank, we'll be there in 10 minutes.

773
01:16:54,177 --> 01:16:55,872
Can you make it any faster?

774
01:16:55,873 --> 01:16:58,556
- We'll do our best.
- Thank you.

775
01:18:51,686 --> 01:18:53,595
Buy tickets for all of us.

776
01:18:53,702 --> 01:18:55,237
Where to?

777
01:18:55,238 --> 01:18:59,205
Anywhere this train is going. We need
to keep moving for half an hour.

778
01:18:59,206 --> 01:19:01,540
Why don't we just keep
driving around?

779
01:19:06,471 --> 01:19:08,293
Another day.

780
01:19:21,734 --> 01:19:24,603
Sir! There!

781
01:19:40,647 --> 01:19:44,839
- Out. Out!
- Everybody out!

782
01:19:44,840 --> 01:19:46,661
- Come on.
- Move!

783
01:19:46,920 --> 01:19:48,862
Move, quick!

784
01:20:05,641 --> 01:20:07,714
- Mr. Minister?
- Yes.

785
01:20:07,850 --> 01:20:09,954
Someone wants to talk to you.

786
01:20:10,762 --> 01:20:13,794
- Papa.
- Are you all right?

787
01:20:17,706 --> 01:20:19,778
Don't sign.

788
01:20:19,978 --> 01:20:23,392
What you have is 15 minutes.

789
01:20:29,898 --> 01:20:32,681
- You ever find out what this is about?
- Garbage.

790
01:20:32,682 --> 01:20:34,623
How much garbage are we talking?

791
01:20:35,050 --> 01:20:38,665
Enough to pollute half the country
for a hundred years.

792
01:20:38,666 --> 01:20:40,095
Try it again.

793
01:20:59,500 --> 01:21:02,955
For a modern woman,
you are very uninformed.

794
01:21:02,956 --> 01:21:05,029
This is the new world.

795
01:21:05,676 --> 01:21:08,267
There are no more countries.
That's old think.

796
01:21:08,268 --> 01:21:11,691
There are just economic realities.
Profit and loss.

797
01:21:11,692 --> 01:21:14,508
Efficiency and waste.

798
01:21:14,509 --> 01:21:16,898
Think global, not local.

799
01:21:17,196 --> 01:21:19,530
Think this.

800
01:21:33,261 --> 01:21:35,628
- Yes?
- Where are we?

801
01:21:42,446 --> 01:21:44,354
We're almost there.

802
01:21:46,414 --> 01:21:47,916
Where?

803
01:21:47,917 --> 01:21:50,339
Here. He is on a train.

804
01:21:50,478 --> 01:21:52,910
- And where are we?
- Here.

805
01:21:52,911 --> 01:21:55,495
We can get units there.

806
01:21:56,623 --> 01:21:58,825
That's a good idea. Do that.

807
01:22:02,159 --> 01:22:05,356
Oh, Frank, come on.

808
01:22:35,472 --> 01:22:38,128
Mr. Minister, I assure you,
everything is in order.

809
01:22:38,163 --> 01:22:40,336
I'm sure it is.

810
01:22:40,337 --> 01:22:44,493
- If there are any problems...
- I know you will solve them.

811
01:22:44,912 --> 01:22:47,213
Now, if you don't mind...

812
01:23:15,889 --> 01:23:19,751
You might not believe this,
but I am, at heart, a pacifist.

813
01:23:20,497 --> 01:23:22,952
I hate violence.

814
01:23:24,403 --> 01:23:27,565
It creates more problems
than it solves.

815
01:23:28,659 --> 01:23:31,856
You know, I never wanted
to do any of this.

816
01:23:32,818 --> 01:23:36,210
A client asked me to obtain a result...

817
01:23:36,211 --> 01:23:38,417
...so I went about creating
an environment...

818
01:23:38,418 --> 01:23:40,306
...with the least amount
of bloodshed.

819
01:23:40,307 --> 01:23:43,122
No one wanted to cooperate.
Not you, not the first driver...

820
01:23:43,123 --> 01:23:47,214
...not your father, not the
recently deceased Frank Martin.

821
01:23:47,827 --> 01:23:50,762
Everyone wanted to fight.

822
01:24:05,045 --> 01:24:06,669
What's so funny?

823
01:24:07,380 --> 01:24:10,248
Hearing a dead man talking.

824
01:26:17,210 --> 01:26:19,481
One more step, Frank.

825
01:26:19,482 --> 01:26:21,424
Come on. One more.

826
01:27:02,780 --> 01:27:04,508
Look.

827
01:27:04,509 --> 01:27:05,970
It's over.

828
01:27:06,364 --> 01:27:08,437
Two minutes to 9. He signed.

829
01:27:11,613 --> 01:27:14,099
Oh, my God.

830
01:27:18,684 --> 01:27:20,538
No, Frank. No, no.

831
01:27:59,391 --> 01:28:02,205
It's over, Frank. It's over.

832
01:28:02,943 --> 01:28:05,789
Mission accomplished.
You and the girl are free to go.

833
01:28:06,847 --> 01:28:09,278
Matter of fact,
I'm so impressed by your talent...

834
01:28:09,279 --> 01:28:11,070
...I'd like to offer you a position.

835
01:28:11,071 --> 01:28:14,714
I'd like to offer you one.
Permanently disabled.

836
01:28:32,737 --> 01:28:34,208
I hate to waste talent.

837
01:28:34,209 --> 01:28:36,608
But I really don't think
we'd make a very good fit.

838
01:28:36,643 --> 01:28:38,517
That's right.

839
01:29:00,865 --> 01:29:02,392
No!

840
01:29:05,698 --> 01:29:09,211
We wouldn't fit, but you and the
bracelet were made for each other.

841
01:29:13,122 --> 01:29:14,811
No, no.

842
01:29:25,187 --> 01:29:26,648
No!

843
01:29:27,747 --> 01:29:29,404
No!

844
01:29:44,003 --> 01:29:46,272
You're doing the right thing.

845
01:30:04,836 --> 01:30:06,974
Valentina.

846
01:30:11,429 --> 01:30:13,086
Valentina.

847
01:30:22,501 --> 01:30:25,020
Am I in heaven?

848
01:30:26,157 --> 01:30:27,457
No...

849
01:30:27,557 --> 01:30:30,208
Looks more like we're in hell.

850
01:30:30,214 --> 01:30:32,260
I don't care.

851
01:30:32,261 --> 01:30:34,334
As long as we're there together.

852
01:30:45,702 --> 01:30:46,917
Yes?

853
01:30:46,918 --> 01:30:50,431
Mr. Minister,
your daughter is in good hands.

854
01:30:51,398 --> 01:30:53,404
Thank you.

855
01:31:06,856 --> 01:31:09,350
- What are you doing?
- What you said, the right thing.

856
01:31:09,351 --> 01:31:12,646
And now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a conference to address...

857
01:31:12,647 --> 01:31:15,654
...on the dangers of doing business
with people like you.

858
01:31:15,655 --> 01:31:17,084
Thank you very much.

859
01:31:35,016 --> 01:31:36,200
Is the launch ready?

860
01:31:36,201 --> 01:31:38,916
- It's on the water, sir, waiting.
- Time to leave.

861
01:31:39,145 --> 01:31:40,901
- Grab the log.
- Okay.

862
01:31:58,761 --> 01:32:01,705
I just don't understand it.

863
01:32:01,706 --> 01:32:03,785
When I was a boy, my father and I...

864
01:32:03,786 --> 01:32:07,177
...used to pull fish out of
this very spot all day long.

865
01:32:07,178 --> 01:32:09,218
Times change, inspector.

866
01:32:09,322 --> 01:32:11,459
As do people.

867
01:32:13,866 --> 01:32:16,201
You referring to me?

868
01:32:17,226 --> 01:32:19,714
I don't think that's
a very accurate statement.

869
01:32:20,138 --> 01:32:22,473
I drive the same car,
live in the same house.

870
01:32:22,474 --> 01:32:26,915
Oh, I was not referring
to your car or your house.

871
01:32:29,195 --> 01:32:31,658
The sea is so restful.

872
01:32:31,659 --> 01:32:33,250
Is lunch ready yet?

873
01:32:33,996 --> 01:32:37,354
Mademoiselle, there is
a certain progression to things.

874
01:32:37,355 --> 01:32:40,746
In order to eat the lunch,
you first have to catch the lunch.

875
01:32:40,747 --> 01:32:43,082
And if we keep talking
instead of concentrating...

876
01:32:43,083 --> 01:32:44,554
...we're gonna catch nothing.

877
01:32:44,555 --> 01:32:48,330
I have better idea. Why we
don't skip catching of lunch...

878
01:32:48,331 --> 01:32:50,379
...and go right to eating of lunch?

879
01:32:50,380 --> 01:32:53,611
I know wonderful place
just up coast from here...

880
01:32:53,612 --> 01:32:56,553
...where they make fish stew.
Incredible.

881
01:32:56,588 --> 01:33:02,599
They use tomatoes and onions,
and little amount of wild lavender.

882
01:33:02,796 --> 01:33:04,811
What kind of wine?

883
01:33:04,812 --> 01:33:06,950
Pink. From south.

884
01:33:07,724 --> 01:33:09,932
A Chteauneuf, perhaps.

885
01:33:09,933 --> 01:33:12,460
- Chilled?
- Of course, chilled.

886
01:33:12,461 --> 01:33:14,796
And for dessert?

